subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head-body 126-141 mm, tail 79-95 mm, ear 23-25 mm, hindfoot 32-34 mm; weight 52-116 g (mean 80 g). Males and females are the same size. See general characters of the genus under the North-western Conyrat (
R. caurinus
) account. The Hairy-soled Conyrat is large and soft-furred, with enormous eyes, moderately short tail, long rather furry ears, and tuft of pale fur at bases of ears. Soles of hindfeet are furry, and first and fifth toes are very short, not reaching beyond bases of middle three toes. Soles are more densely haired than in the Naked-soled Conyrat (
R. typicus
); tail is bicolored. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 34, FN = 32.
